3 Process of creating FE model of the tibia
The process of creating an FE model of the tibia is as follows: 1 The tibia of a 27-year-old male weighing 60 kg with tibia length of 30 cm and the
area of the top of the tibia of 2795 mm2 is shown in Figure 2. 2 Multi-section solid command is used to get different cross-sections. 3 The fibula bone is a supporting bone to the tibia; the forces acting on it is neglected,
since load transmitted to the fibula bone is neglected. 4 Later, cut the top of the tibia with a surface having the same profile as that of the
tibial surface. 5 Later, it is saved in the iges.file format.
